                            <comment id="10224" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Tue, 16 Mar 2004 01:10:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a funny issue: WebLogic can&apos;t load the DisposableBean interface that the destroyBean method checks for?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Indeed, a workaround would be to load the DisposableBean interface in a static initializer in AbstractBeanFactory. It just seems weird to have to do this.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10225" author="asenft" created="Tue, 16 Mar 2004 17:12:16 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;It is weird, indeed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An additional information (maybe someone can reproduce that also): The problem occurs only on redeployment of an already deployed application.&lt;br/&gt;
Stopping the application followed by a deployment does not produce the error. (All operations triggered via the administration console)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Andreas&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10228" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 17 Mar 2004 03:59:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Eagerly loading the DisposableBean class in a static block within AbstractAutowireCapableBeanFactory now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10756" author="mickeys6" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2004 13:37:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is also an issue in:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;org/springframework/context/support/AbstractApplicationContext.java&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;but with the ContextClosedEvent.class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10757" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Wed, 11 Aug 2004 02:53:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for spotting this! I&apos;ve just added a static block that preloads the ContextClosedEvent class in AbstractApplicationContext.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
